Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,, unrealistic: adj. 不真实\N Lesson 12. Life on a desert island. Most of us have formed an unrealistic picture of life on a desert island.\N第12课。在荒岛上的生活。我们大多数人在荒岛上构成了生活不切实际。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.50,0:00:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,, paradise: n.   天堂，乐士\N We sometimes imagine a desert island to be a sort of paradise where the sun always shines.\N我们有时会想象一个荒岛是一种天堂，太阳总是闪耀。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.00,0:00:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,, Life there is simple and good. Ripe fruit falls from the trees and you never have to work.\N生活是简单而美好的。成熟的水果从树上掉下来，您永远不必工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.30,0:00:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,, The other side of the picture is quite the opposite.\N图片的另一侧恰恰相反。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.50,0:00:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,, wretched: adj. 可怜的，艰苦的, starve: v.   挨饿\N Life on a desert island is wretched. You either starve to death or live like Robinson Crusoe.\N荒岛上的生活很可怜。您要么饿死，要么像鲁滨逊·克鲁索（Robinson Crusoe）一样生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.00,0:00:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,, element: n.   成分\N Waiting for a boat which never comes. Perhaps there is an element of truth in both these pictures.\N等待一条永不来的船。这两张图片中都有一个真理的元素。
